{"SUI GENERIS":[{"def":"Of his or its own kind.","pos":""}],"SUICIDAL":[{"def":"Partaking of, or of the nature of, the crime or suicide.","pos":""}],"SUICIDE":[{"def":"The act of taking one's own life voluntary and intentionally; self-murder; specifically (Law), the felonious killing of one's self; the deliberate and intentional destruction of one's own life by a person of years of discretion and of sound mind.","pos":""},{"def":"One guilty of self-murder; a felo-de-se.","pos":""}],"SUICIDISM":[{"def":"The quality or state of being suicidal, or self-murdering.","pos":""}],"SUICISM":[{"def":"Selfishness; egoism.","pos":""}],"SUILLAGE":[{"def":"A drain or collection of filth.","pos":""}],"SUILLINE":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a hog or the Hog family (Suidæ).","pos":""}],"SUINE":[{"def":"A mixture of oleomargarine with lard or other fatty ingredients.","pos":""}],"SUING":[{"def":"The process of soaking through anything.","pos":""}],"SUINGLY":[{"def":"In succession; afterwards.","pos":""}],"SUINT":[{"def":"A peculiar substance obtained from the wool of sheep, consisting largely of potash mixed with fatty and earthy matters.","pos":""}],"SUIOGOTHS":[{"def":"The Scandinavian Goths.","pos":""}],"SUIST":[{"def":"One who seeks for things which gratify merely himself; a selfish person; a selfist.","pos":""}],"SUIT":[{"def":"The attempt to gain an end by legal process; an action or process for the recovery of a right or claim; legal application to a court for justice; prosecution of right before any tribunal; as, a civil suit; a criminal suit; a suit in chancery.","pos":""},{"def":"One of the four sets of cards which constitute a pack; -- each set consisting of thirteen cards bearing a particular emblem, as hearts, spades, cubs, or diamonds.","pos":""}],"SUITABILITY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being suitable; suitableness.","pos":""}],"SUITABLE":[{"def":"Capable of suiting; fitting; accordant; proper; becoming; agreeable; adapted; as, ornaments suitable to one's station; language suitable for the subject.","pos":""}],"SUITE":[{"def":"One of the old musical forms, before the time of the more compact sonata, consisting of a string or series of pieces all in the same key, mostly in various dance rhythms, with sometimes an elaborate prelude.","pos":""}],"SUITING":[{"def":"Among tailors, cloth suitable for making entire suits of clothes.","pos":""}],"SUITOR":[{"def":"One who sues, petitions, or entreats; a petitioner; an applicant.","pos":""},{"def":"Especially, one who solicits a woman in marriage; a wooer; a lover.","pos":""}],"SUITRESS":[{"def":"A female supplicant.","pos":""}]}